{"sections":[],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"}],"symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"extendedModule":"GIO","roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","title":"init_(cancellable:)","externalID":"s:3GIO16InitableProtocolPAAE5init_11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO17DBusConnectionRefV"},"abstract":[{"text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"init_","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","text":"CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method is intended for language bindings. If writing in C,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_initable_new()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" should typically be used instead.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The object must be initialized before any real use after initial","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"construction, either with this function or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_async_initable_init_async()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementations may also support cancellation. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" is not ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then initialization can be cancelled by triggering the cancellable object","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from another thread. If the operation was cancelled, the error"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. If "},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the object doesn’t support cancellable initialization the error","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"notSupported","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be returned.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If the object is not initialized, or initialization returns with an","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"error, then all operations on the object except ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are considered to be invalid, and have undefined"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behaviour. See the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","isActive":true},{"text":" for more details.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Callers should not assume that a class which implements ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","isActive":true},{"text":" can be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"initialized multiple times, unless the class explicitly documents itself as","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"supporting this. Generally, a class’ implementation of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init()"},{"text":" can assume","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(and assert) that it will only be called once. Previously, this documentation","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"recommended all ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" implementations should be idempotent; that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"recommendation was relaxed in GLib 2.54."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If a class explicitly supports being initialized multiple times, it is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recommended that the method is idempotent: multiple calls with the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"arguments should return the same results. Only the first call initializes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the object; further calls return the result of the first call.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"One reason why a class might need to support idempotent initialization is if","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it is designed to be used via the singleton pattern, with a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObjectClass.constructor"},{"type":"text","text":" that sometimes returns an existing instance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"In this pattern, a caller would expect to be able to call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_initable_init()"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on the result of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_new()"},{"text":", regardless of whether it is in fact a new","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"instance.","type":"text"}]}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionRef\/InitableProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/dbusconnectionref\/init_(cancellable:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionRef\/init_(cancellable:)"},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusConnectionRef/init_(cancellable:)":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionRef\/init_(cancellable:)","title":"init_(cancellable:)","type":"topic","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"init_","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"text":"?) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusconnectionref\/init_(cancellable:)","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface.","type":"text"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"#iface@Gio.Initable#description":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"description"}],"title":"description","identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","url":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","type":"link"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/AsyncInitable":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","title":"AsyncInitable","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/asyncinitable","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"code":"GAsyncInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is an interface for asynchronously initializable objects."}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusConnectionRef":{"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusconnectionref","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GDBusConnection","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type is used for D-Bus connections to remote","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"peers such as a message buses."}],"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"DBusConnectionRef","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"DBusConnectionRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionRef","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DBusConnectionRef"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DBusConnectionRef/InitableProtocol-Implementations":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnectionRef\/InitableProtocol-Implementations","abstract":[],"kind":"article","title":"InitableProtocol Implementations","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/dbusconnectionref\/initableprotocol-implementations","type":"topic","role":"collectionGroup"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Initable":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/initable","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Initable","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Initable","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" is implemented by objects that can fail during"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"initialization. If an object implements this interface then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it must be initialized as the first thing after construction,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"either via [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Initable.init"},{"text":"] or [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.init_async"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(the latter is only available if it also implements [iface","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"])."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Initable"}]}}}